div.p:
For that purpose they have appointed their Plenipotentiaries, to-wit: 

The President of the United States: John Hay, Secretary of State of
                            the United States;

The President of Haiti: Mr. J. N. Léger, Envoy Extraordinary and
                            Minister Plenipotentiary of Haiti at Washington;

And whereas the said treaty has been duly ratified on both parts, and the
                    ratifications of the two governments were exchanged in the City of Washington,
                    on the nineteenth day of March, one thousand nine hundred and four;
